<Link id="l00029" /><CodeLine lineNumber="29"><Highlight kind="comment">/// SparseBitVector is an implementation of a bitvector that is sparse by only</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00030" /><CodeLine lineNumber="30"><Highlight kind="comment">/// storing the elements that have non-zero bits set.  In order to make this</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00031" /><CodeLine lineNumber="31"><Highlight kind="comment">/// fast for the most common cases, SparseBitVector is implemented as a linked</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00032" /><CodeLine lineNumber="32"><Highlight kind="comment">/// list of SparseBitVectorElements.  We maintain a pointer to the last</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00033" /><CodeLine lineNumber="33"><Highlight kind="comment">/// SparseBitVectorElement accessed (in the form of a list iterator), in order</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00034" /><CodeLine lineNumber="34"><Highlight kind="comment">/// to make multiple in-order test/set constant time after the first one is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00035" /><CodeLine lineNumber="35"><Highlight kind="comment">/// executed.  Note that using vectors to store SparseBitVectorElement&#39;s does</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00036" /><CodeLine lineNumber="36"><Highlight kind="comment">/// not work out very well because it causes insertion in the middle to take</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00037" /><CodeLine lineNumber="37"><Highlight kind="comment">/// enormous amounts of time with a large amount of bits.  Other structures that</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00038" /><CodeLine lineNumber="38"><Highlight kind="comment">/// have better worst cases for insertion in the middle (various balanced trees,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00039" /><CodeLine lineNumber="39"><Highlight kind="comment">/// etc) do not perform as well in practice as a linked list with this iterator</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00040" /><CodeLine lineNumber="40"><Highlight kind="comment">/// kept up to date.  They are also significantly more memory intensive.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00041" /><CodeLine lineNumber="41"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00711" /><CodeLine lineNumber="711"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">while</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (Iter2 != RHS2.Elements.end()) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
